===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# [[ritual]]; [[rite]]; [[ceremony]]
#: {{zh-x|婚禮|wedding}}
#: {{zh-x|喪{sāng}禮|funeral}}
#* {{zh-x|我 孔 熯{shàn} 矣、式 禮 莫 愆。|We are very much exhausted, and have performed every '''ceremony''' without error.|ref=Shijing}}
#* {{zh-x|卒 廷 見 ^相{xiāng}-如，畢 禮 而 歸 之。|In the end, ({{w|King Zhaoxiang of Qin}}) granted {{w|Lin Xiangru|(Lin) Xiangru}} an audience at his court, completed the '''ceremonies''', and sent him back.|ref=Shiji}}
# [[rule]]s of [[etiquette]]; [[rule]]s of [[propriety]]
#* {{zh-x|夫子 循循 然 善誘 人，博 我 以 文，約 我 以 禮。|The Master, by orderly method, skillfully leads men on. He enlarged my mind with learning, and taught me the '''restraints of propriety'''.|ref=Analects}}
#* {{zh-x|夫{fú} 禮 者，所以 定 親疏，決 嫌疑，別 同異，明 是非 也。|
They are the '''rules of propriety''', that furnish the means of determining (the observances towards) relatives, as near and remote; of settling points which may cause suspicion or doubt; of distinguishing where there should be agreement, and where difference; and of making clear what is right and what is wrong.|ref=Liji}}
# [[courtesy]]; [[etiquette]]; [[manners]]
#: {{zh-x|敬禮|to salute}}
#: {{zh-x|禮多人不怪|nobody will find fault with extra courtesy}}
# [[present#Noun|present]]; [[gift]] {{zh-mw|m,c:份}}
#: {{zh-x|禮物|gift}}
# to [[treat]] with [[respect]] and [[courtesy]]
#: {{zh-x|敬賢禮士|to '''treat''' worthies and intellectuals respectfully and '''courteously'''}}
# 48th [[tetragram]] of the {{w|Taixuanjing}}; "ritual" ([[𝌵]])
# {{surname|zh}}

====Usage notes====
Usually, a single {{zh-l|禮}} refers to a gift that involves more serious social interaction. For gifts between friends, {{zh-l|禮物}} is used instead.

